<main id="content" class="content"> <header> <h1 class="title">For Sheri</h1>
 <p class="subtitle" role="doc-subtitle">Jan 13, 2015 00:00</p>
</header> <p>
For Sheri on her birthday:
</p>

 <p>
“Did you get <br></br>
a good-morning <br></br>
kiss?” <br></br></p>

 <p>
I ask.
</p>

 <p>
“No, I don’t think so.”
</p>

 <p>
You reply, <br></br>
even though I <br></br>
know that’s not true.
</p>

 <p>
Some couples won’t <br></br>
speak for years <br></br>
because of some <br></br>
small lie.
</p>

 <p>
So, how do <br></br>
I feel?
</p>

 <p>
Like a kid <br></br>
who just heard
</p>

 <p>
“No school - it’s <br></br>
a snow day today.” <br></br></p>

 <p>
Like a person <br></br>
who reached into <br></br>
his jacket pocket <br></br>
on the first day <br></br>
of fall,
</p>

 <p>
and pulled out <br></br>
two twenty-dollar <br></br>
bills.
</p>

 <p>
Those people just <br></br>
think they have <br></br>
all the luck.
</p>

 <p>
I know better <br></br>
though, <br></br></p>

 <p>
because it’s <br></br>
been over <br></br>
thirty years, <br></br></p>

 <p>
and
</p>

 <p>
just one kiss <br></br>
is still <br></br>
not enough.
</p>


